280","1235–1280":"1235–1280","1228–Female":"1228–Overleden","1235–Male":"1235–Overleden","1257–Female":"1257–Overleden","1280–Male":"1280–Overleden","1200–1266":"1200–1266","1186–Female":"1186–Overleden","abt 1235":"circa 1235","1228":"1228","1257":"1257","1235":"1235","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","before 1265":"vóór 1265","about 1257":"circa 1257","1186":"1186","Abt 1235":"circa 1235","Abt 1280":"circa 1280","1280":"1280","Wingfield, Suffolk, England":"Wingfield, Suffolk, England","Suffolk Co., Eng.":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Suffolk, Eng.":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bowsley, Antley, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"Abt 1235–1280":"about 1235–1280","1235–1280":"1235–1280","1228–Female":"1228–Deceased","1235–Male":"1235–Deceased","1257–Female":"1257–Deceased","1280–Male":"1280–Deceased","1200–1266":"1200–1266","1186–Female":"1186–Deceased","abt 1235":"about 1235","1228":"1228","1257":"1257","1235":"1235","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","before 1265":"before 1265","about 1257":"about 1257","1186":"1186","Abt 1235":"about 1235","Abt 1280":"about 1280","1280":"1280","Wingfield, Suffolk, England":"Wingfield, Suffolk, England","Suffolk Co., Eng.":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","of Suffolk, Eng.":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bowsley, Antley, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Glanville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Cornwall and Devon): of Norman origin, a habitational name from a place so called in Calvados, France, named from an ancient Germanic personal name of uncertain form and meaning + Old French <i>ville</i> ‘settlement’. This name has frequently been confused with <b>Glanfield</b>, a habitational name from Glanvill Farm in Devon, Clanville in Somerset and Hampshire, or Clanfield in Hampshire, or from some other place likewise named with Old English <i>clǣne</i> ‘clean’ (i.e. free of brambles and undergrowth) + <i>feld</i> ‘pasture, open country’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Gilbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. This was the name of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilbert Glanville was born about 1235, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Gilbert Glanville, was 37 and his mother, Mrs. Gilbert De Glanville, was 51. He married Isobel de Glanville before 1265, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died in 1280, at the age of 46."},"et":{"Abt 1235–1280":"umbes 1235–1280","1235–1280":"1235–1280","1228–Female":"1228–Surnud","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1257–Female":"1257–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1200–1266":"1200–1266","1186–Female":"1186–Surnud","abt 1235":"umbes 1235","1228":"1228","1257":"1257","1235":"1235","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","before 1265":"enne 1265","about 1257":"umbes 1257","1186":"1186","Abt 1235":"umbes 1235","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1280":"1280","Wingfield, Suffolk, England":"Wingfield, Suffolk, England","Suffolk Co., Eng.":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Suffolk, Eng.":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bowsley, Antley, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1235–1280":"noin 1235–1280","1235–1280":"123